fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
We will show \vec {0}\in \mathop {	extrm {ran}}
olimits (L) and \mathop {	extrm {ran}}
olimits (L) is closed under vector addition and scalar multiplication, then the Criteria for subset to be a subspace implies \mathop {	extrm {ran}}
olimits (L) is a subspace of W.

Let w_{1},w_{2}\in \mathop {\textrm {ran}}\nolimits (L). Then there exists v_{1},v_{2}\in  V such that L(v_{1})=w_{1} and L(v_{2})=w_{2}. Then
L(v_{1}+v_{2})=L(v_{1})+L(v_{2})=w_{1}+w_{2}
Hence w_{1}+w_{2}\in \mathop {\textrm {ran}}\nolimits (L), which implies it is closed under vector addition.

There is an m\times  n matrix with entries in \mathbb {F}
M(L)=\begin {pmatrix}a_{11} & … & a_{1n}\\\vdots & \ddots  &\vdots \\a_{m1}&…&a_{mn}\end {pmatrix}
where
L(v_{j})=a_{1j}w_{1}+…+a_{mj}w_{m}
for j=1,…,n.
